						<div class="postbody">He (Disch) works with unsigned samples, I would say the 'nostalgic side'. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />
<br />On my side, read - if the channel is disabled by any reason, the output is obviously zero; otherwise, it can be +Value or -Value. 
<br />
<br />There's 2 sample sizes: 8-bit and 16-bit (umm... yeah). If you choose the 8-bit form, then values are -128 up to +127; else, the 16-bit assumes -32768 up to +32767 (signed int). You're the judge - there's no right choice.</div>

					
