					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As long as your overall audio level never exceeds 0x7F, you should be okay - otherwise, you will experience some wicked clipping as a result.
<br />
<br />If you need to output a "centered" waveform, you should output 0 for silence and +/- VOL when the wave is playing. It may not perfectly represent the waveform coming out of a real NES, but it will sound almost exactly the same.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
